Project Description: Pharmaceutical SaaS Web Application
This project outlines the development of a comprehensive Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) web application tailored for a pharmaceutical company. The application aims to streamline critical business operations by integrating several key functionalities into a single, intuitive platform.

1. Project Goal:
To develop a robust, scalable, and user-friendly SaaS web application that centralizes inventory, employee, HR, and customer relationship management for a pharmaceutical company, enhancing operational efficiency and data accessibility.

2. Scope of Work:

The development will encompass the following core modules:

Inventory Management System:

Tracking of pharmaceutical products (raw materials, finished goods).

Management of stock levels, reorder points, and expiry dates.

Batch and lot number tracking.

Reporting on inventory movement and valuation.

Employee Management System:

Employee data management (personal details, roles, contact information).

Salary calculation and payroll processing.

Commission tracking and calculation.

Bonus management and distribution.

Attendance and leave management.

Basic HR Management:

Employee onboarding and offboarding processes.

Document management (contracts, performance reviews).

Basic reporting on HR metrics.

Customer Relationship Management (CRM):

Management of customer and client profiles.

Tracking of interactions, sales history, and communication logs.

Lead and opportunity management.

Reporting on customer engagement and sales performance.

3. Technology Stack:

Backend: Django Framework

API: RESTful APIs

Frontend: React

Styling: Tailwind CSS
